07 />\n|align=center|F\n|{{dts|format=dmy|1889|02|20}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2002|01|03}}\n|{{ayd|1889|02|20|2002|01|03}}\n|(unknown)\n|Iwate\n|-\n|rowspan=2|95\n|data-sort-value=\"Kimura, Hanae\"|Hanae Kimura<ref name=GRG-2015 />\n|align=center|F\n|{{dts|format=dmy|1901|08|08}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2014|06|16}}\n|rowspan=2 | {{ayd|1901|08|08|2014|06|16}}\n|(unknown)\n|Tokushima\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"Koide\"|Yasutaro Koide<ref name=GRG-Deceased />\n|align=center|M\n|{{dts|format=dmy|1903|03|13}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2016|01|19}}\n|[[Fukui Prefecture|Fukui]]\n|Aichi\n|-\n|97\n|data-sort-value=\"Yonehara\"|Yoki Yonehara<ref name=GRG-Japan-2007 />\n|align=center|F\n|{{dts|format=dmy|1892|03|02}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2005|01|04}}\n|{{ayd|1892|03|02|2005|01|04}}\n|(unknown)\n|Shimane\n|- bgcolor=#99FF99\n|  bgcolor=#F9F9F9 align=right data-sort-value=97.5 | \n| data-sort-value=\"Baba\" | Yoshi Baba<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news24.jp/sp/nnn/news16503536.html|title=\u9803\u5185\u306e100\u60f3\u4ee5\u4e0a\u306e\u304a\u5e74\u5bc4\u30a6\u306f725\u4eba|website=news24.jp |date=13 September 2019|lang=ja |trans-title= There are 725 centenarians in the prefecture|accessdate=14 September 2019}}</ref>\n|align=center|F\n|{{dts|format=dmy|1907|06|03}}\n|Living\n|{{ayd|1907|06|03}}\n|(unknown)\n|[[Yamanashi Prefecture|Yamanashi]]\n|-\n|98\n|data-sort-value=\"Nakae\"|Hiro Nakae<ref name=\"GRG Deaths in 2011\"/>\n|align=center|F\n|{{dts|format=dmy|1898|10|20}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2011|08|19}}\n|{{ayd|1898|10|20|2011|08|19}}\n|(unknown)\n|Hiroshima\n|-\n|99\n|data-sort-value=\"Tamagawa\"|Suma Tamagawa<ref name=\"GRG Deaths in 2011\"/>\n|align=center|F\n|{{dts|format=dmy|1899|03|14}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2011|12|23}}\n|{{ayd|1899|03|14|2011|12|23}}\n|(unknown)\n|Iwate\n|-\n|rowspan=2|100\n|data-sort-value=\"Kouno\"|Yoneno Kouno<ref name=GRG-Deceased />\n|align=center|F\n|{{dts|format=dmy|1902|08|07}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2015|04|24}}\n|rowspan=2 | {{ayd|1902|08|07|2015|04|24}}\n|(unknown)\n|[[Ehime Prefecture|Ehime]]\n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"Suzuki\"|Mine Suzuki<ref name=GRG-Deceased />\n|align=center|F\n|{{dts|format=dmy|1905|03|26}}\n|{{dts|format=dmy|2017|12|11}}\n|(unknown)\n|Chiba\n|}\n\n== Biographies ==\n\n=== Denzo Ishizaki ===\n{{Nihongo|'''Denzo Ishizaki'''|\u77f3\u5d0e \u4f1d\u8535|Ishizaki Denz\u014d|20 October 1886 \u2013 29 April 1999}} was for a short time Japan's oldest living person and [[Oldest people|the world's oldest living man]], from February to April 1999, and when he died the oldest Japanese man ever until being surpassed by Yukichi Chuganji on 30 September 2001.<ref name=\"Denzo Ishizaki\">{{cite news|title=Deaths Elsewhere - Denzo Ishizaki |url=http://articles.baltimoresun.com/1999-05-02/news/9905040357_1_cancer-meritt-retirement-home |newspaper=[[The Baltimore Sun]] |date=2 May 1999 |accessdate=14 September 2015}}</ref> A former elementary school teacher and town assembly member, Ishizaki lived in Kansago, [[Ibaraki Prefecture]], where he died of [[multiple organ failure]] on 29 April 1999 at the age of 112 years, 191 days.<ref>{{cite news |title=DENZO ISHIZAKI |url=http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1999-04-30/news/9904300138_1_ishizaki-rory-calhoun-great-john-l |newspaper=Orlando Sentinel |date=30 April 1999 |accessdate=14 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== Nabi Tajima ===\n{{Nihongo|'''Nabi Tajima'''|\u7530\u5cf6 \u30ca\u30d3|Tajima Nabi|4 August 1900 \u2013 21 April 2018}}<ref>{{Cite news |author=Schumann, Rebecka |title=Misao Okawa, The World\u2019s Oldest Woman, And 39 Other Female Supercentenarians |newspaper=International Business Times |date=9 June 2014 |url=http://www.ibtimes.com/misao-okawa-worlds-oldest-woman-39-other-female-supercentenarians-1596262 |accessdate=7 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20180421/k10011413001000.html | title=Worlds oldest age 117-year-old Tashima Navi died | access-date=1 April 2019 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180421225231/https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20180421/k10011413001000.html | archive-date=21 April 2018 | url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |title=Guinness World Records 2015 |date=11 September 2014 |page=[https://archive.org/details/guinnessworldrec0000unse_f8z3/page/77 77] |publisher=Guinness World Records |isbn=978-1-9088-4370-8 |url=https://archive.org/details/guinnessworldrec0000unse_f8z3|url-access=registration }}</ref> followed [[Violet Brown]] as the world's oldest person for 217 days after 16 September 2017. She was the last surviving person from the 19th century and the [[Lost Generation]].<!-- Notice: Although the 19th century and the Lost Generation both ended in the same year (1900), they do not have the same time span. The 19th century included the years 1801-1882, but not the Lost Generation which begins with 1883.--><ref name=slate>Daniel Politi, [https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2018/04/the-last-known-person-born-in-the-19th-century-died-in-japan.html The Last Known Person Born in the 19th Century Dies in Japan at 117], ''[[Slate Magazine]]'', 22 April 2018.</ref> She died at age 117 years and 260 days and is the [[Oldest people#Ten oldest verified people ever|third-oldest person ever]]. Tajima is the oldest Asian to be validated by modern standards.<ref name=3rd>{{cite web|url=https://bnonews.com/site/index.php/2018/04/nabi-tajima-becomes-3rd-oldest-person-history-ever/|title=Japanese woman becomes 3rd oldest person in history|work=[[BNO News]]|date=9 April 2018|accessdate=10 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nTajima was born and died on the small island of [[Kikaijima]], about halfway between [[Okinawa]] and the main Japanese islands. Her husband, Tominishi Tajima (\u7530\u5cf6 \u5bcc\u4e8c\u5b50), died at the age of 93 in 1991.<ref name=\"Nabi\" /><ref>[http://www.sankei.com/west/news/170915/wst1709150053-n1.html \u5b50\u5b6b\uff11\uff14\uff10\u4eba\u2026\u767a\u9175\u98f2\u6599\u597d\u307f\u3001\u3088\u304f\u98df\u3079\u3000\u56fd\u5185\u6700\u9ad8\u9f62\uff11\uff11\uff17\u6b73\u306e\u7530\u5cf6\u30ca\u30d3\u3055\u3093] {{in lang|ja}}</ref> She had nine children, seven sons and two daughters,<ref name=\"Nabi\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nankainn.com/local/\u300c\u30ca\u30d3\u3070\u3042\u3061\u3083\u3093\u3061\u3070\u308a\u3088\u30fc\u300d\uff0f\u559c\u754c\u753a\u306e\u7530\u5cf6\u3055 |script-title=ja:\u300c\u30ca\u30d3\u3070\u3042\u3061\u3083\u3093\u3061\u3070\u308a\u3088\u30fc\u300d\uff0f\u559c\u754c\u753a\u306e\u7530\u5cf6\u3055\u3093\u306b\u770c\u795d\u3044\u72b6 |trans-title=\"Grandma Nabi\" - Kikai City holds provincial celebration for Mrs. Tajima |language=Japanese |date=16 September 2015 |accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref> and in September 2017 she was reported to have had around 160 descendants, including great-great-great-grandchildren.<ref name=sept2017yahoo>[https://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20170919-00010003-nankainn-l46 117\u6b73\u3000\u4e16\u754c\u4e00\u3078\u770c\u6c11\u6804\u8a89\u691c\u8a0e\u3000\u7530\u5cf6\u30ca\u30d3\u3055\u3093\u3092\u77e5\u4e8b\u8a2a\u554f\u3000\u9e7f\u5150\u5cf6\u770c\u559c\u754c\u753a] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20171028070335/https://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20170919-00010003-nankainn-l46 |date=28 October 2017 }} {{in lang|ja}}</ref> She stated that her longevity was due to sleeping soundly and eating delicious food.<ref name=slate/> Guinness World Records was planning to certify Tajima as the world\u2019s oldest person, but she died at a nursing home in [[Kikai, Kagoshima|Kikai City]] before they could do so.<ref>[https://theworldnews.net/au-news/world-s-oldest-woman-misses-record World\u2019s oldest woman misses record], The World News, 22 April 2018</ref><ref name=wapo-20180422>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/worldviews/wp/2018/04/22/the-worlds-oldest-person-died-at-117-she-was-the-last-known-person-born-in-the-19th-century/ |title=The world\u2019s oldest person died at 117. She was the last known person born in the 19th century. |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |first=Alex |last=Horton |date=22 April 2018 |access-date=8 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Masaz\u014d Nonaka ===\n{{Nihongo|'''Masaz\u014d Nonaka'''|\u91ce\u4e2d \u6b63\u9020|Nonaka Masaz\u014d|25 July 1905 \u2013 20 January 2019}} was, at the time of his death, Japan's oldest living man since October 2016,<ref name=sankei>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sankei.com/life/news/161215/lif1612150042-n1.html|script-title=ja:\u56fd\u5185\u6700\u9ad8\u9f62\uff11\uff11\uff12\u6b73\u306e\u7537\u6027\u6b7b\u53bb\u3000\u6771\u4eac\u306e\u5409\u7530\u6b63\u5149\u3055\u3093|work=\u7523\u7d4c\u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9|publisher=\u7523\u7d4c\u65b0\u805e|date=December 15, 2016|accessdate=April 12, 2018|language=Japanese}}</ref> and the world's oldest living man since January 2018.<ref>http://www.grg.org/GRGNews2019.html</ref> Nonaka was also the oldest person ever born in [[Hokkaido]].\n\nNonaka had two brothers and three sisters; he married Hatsuno Nonaka in 1931. They had five children, of whom three were living as of January 2019.<ref name=\"scmp.com\">[https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/east-asia/article/2182901/japans-masazo-nonaka-declared-worlds-oldest-living-man-2018-dies Japan\u2019s Masazo Nonaka, declared world\u2019s oldest living man in 2018, dies aged 113]</ref> He ran the family ''[[onsen]]'', which opened in 1905, and spent most of his time in a wheelchair, crediting his longevity to eating sweets and relaxing in the hot springs.<ref name=\"sky\">{{cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/worlds-oldest-man-revealed-as-112-year-old-masazo-nonaka-11324957|website=news.sky.com|title=World's oldest man revealed as 112-year-old Masazo Nonaka|accessdate=April 11, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"time\">{{cite news |url=http://time.com/5236018/masazo-nonaka-japan-oldest-person-alive/ |title=The Key to Longevity for the World's Oldest Man Alive? Sumo Wrestling and Hot Springs |magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |agency=[[Associated Press]] |date=11 April 2018 |access-date=10 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180414054451/http://time.com/5236018/masazo-nonaka-japan-oldest-person-alive/ |archive-date=14 April 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Nonaka died at home of natural causes, at 1:30am on 20 January 2019, aged 113 years, 179 days.<ref name=\"scmp.com\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/human-interest/oldest-man-dies-japan-age-113/|title=World's Oldest Man, Who Loved Sweets and Lived at a Hot Springs Inn, Dies in Japan at 113|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=2019-01-30}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Shigechiyo Izumi]]\n{{Portalbar|Biography|Japan|Lists}}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n<ref name=GRG-Living>{{cite web |url=http://supercentenarian-research-foundation.org/TableE.aspx |title=GRG World Supercentenarian Rankings List \u2013 Validated Living Supercentenarians |first1=Louis |last1=Epstein |first2=Robert |last2=Young |first3=Johnny |last3=Adams |first4=Mark |last4=Muir |publisher=[[Gerontology Research Group]] |date=6 January 2020 |access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=GRG-Deceased>{{cite web |url=http://supercentenarian-research-foundation.org/TableE.aspx |title=GRG World Supercentenarian Rankings List \u2013 Validated Deceased Supercentenarians |first1=Louis |last1=Epstein |first2=Robert |last2=Young |first3=Johnny |last3=Adams |first4=Mark |last4=Muir |publisher=[[Gerontology Research Group]] |date=6 January 2020 |access-date=7 January 2020}}</ref>\n<ref name=GRG-2015>{{cite web |url=http://www.grg.org/Adams/G.HTM |title=GRG Database by Nation |first1=Marco |last1=Wikkerink |first2=Waclaw Jan |last2=Kroczek |publisher=[[Gerontology Research Group]] |date=1 January 2015 |access-date=8 November 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=GRG-Japan-2007>{{cite web |url=http://www.grg.org/Adams/L/Japan.htm |title=Verified supercentenarian cases \u2013 Japan |publisher=[[Gerontology Research Group|GRG]] |date=10 April 2007 |access-date=17 December 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"GRG Deaths in 2007\">{{cite web |url=http://www.grg.org/Adams/Deaths2007.htm |title=Deaths for 2007 (in Chronological Order) |publisher=[[Gerontology Research Group|GRG]] |date=24 September 2014 |access-date=9 December 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"GRG Deaths in 2008\">{{cite web |url=http://www.grg.org/Adams/Deaths2008.htm |title=Deaths for 2008 (in Chronological Order) |publisher=[[Gerontology Research Group|GRG]] |date=1 July 2013 |access-date=9 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150705212402/http://www.grg.org/Adams/Deaths2008.htm |archive-date=5 July 2015 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"GRG Deaths in 2009\">{{cite web |url=http://www.grg.org/Adams/Deaths2009.htm |title=Deaths for 2009 (in Chronological Order) |publisher=[[Gerontology Research Group|GRG]] |date=3 December 2014 |access-date=9 December 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"GRG Deaths in 2010\">{{cite web |url=http://www.grg.org/Adams/Deaths2010.htm |title=Deaths for 2010 (in Chronological Order) |publisher=[[Gerontology Research Group|GRG]] |date=18 September 2014 |access-date=9 December 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"GRG Deaths in 2011\">{{cite web |url=http://www.grg.org/Adams/Deaths2011.htm |title=Deaths for 2011 (in Chronological Order) |publisher=[[Gerontology Research Group|GRG]] |date=17 November 2014 |access-date=9 December 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"GRG Deaths in 2012\">{{cite web |url=http://www.grg.org/Adams/Deaths2012.htm |title=Deaths for 2012 (in Chronological Order) |publisher=[[Gerontology Research Group|GRG]] |date=4 November 2014 |access-date=9 December 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Longevity}}\n\n[[Category:Japanese supercentenarians| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of Japanese people|Supercentenarians]]\n[[Category:Lists of supercentenarians by nationality|Japanese]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n[[File:Chiyono Hasegawa September 2010.jpg|thumb|upright|Chiyono Hasegawa (1896\u20132011), a resident of [[Saga Prefecture|Saga]], was one of hundreds of Japanese women to have lived past 110 years. She is pictured here in September 2010. She was the oldest person in Japan and second oldest in the world, dying at 115 years, 12 days.]]\n\n'''Japanese supercentenarians''' are citizens, residents or emigrants from Japan who have attained or surpassed 110 years of age. {{As of|January 2015}}, the [[Gerontology Research Group]] (GRG) had validated the longevity claims of 318 Japanese [[supercentenarian]]s, most of them women.<ref name=GRG-2015 /> The oldest Japanese person on record was Nabi Tajima, who died on 21 April 2018 aged 117 years, 260 days. Japan  was also home to the [[List of the verified oldest men|world's oldest man ever]], [[Jiroemon Kimura]], who lived to age 116 years, 54 days.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.kyoto-np.co.jp/politics/article/20130614000084 |script-title=ja:\u3044\u3064\u307e\u3067\u3082\u300c\u8f1d\u304f\u5b9d\u300d\u3067\u3000\u6728\u6751\u6b21\u90ce\u53f3\u885b\u9580\u3055\u3093\u544a\u5225\u5f0f |language=ja |trans-title=Jiroemon Kimura's funeral \u2013 a sparkling jewel forever |date=14 June 2013 |newspaper=[[Kyoto Shimbun]] |access-date=20 October 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615030142/http://www.kyoto-np.co.jp/politics/article/20130614000084 |archive-date=15 June 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAs of {{TODAY}}, the [[List of the oldest living people|oldest living person]] in Japan as well as the world is [[Kane Tanaka]], born 2 January 1903, age {{ayd|2 January 1903}}.<ref name=GRG-Living />\n\n== 100 oldest Japanese people ==\n{{legend2|#F9F9F9|Deceased|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#99FF99|Living|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}<br/>\nEntries without a number have not yet been validated by the [[Gerontology Research Group|GRG]].\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Rank\n!Name \n!Sex\n!Birth date\n!Death date\n!Age\n!Prefecture of birth\n!Prefecture of death <br/> or residence\n|-\n|{{0}}1\n|data-sort-value=\"Tajima\"|[[Nabi Tajima]]<ref n